KW  - Unit roots
KW  - Cointegration
KW  - Fisher effect
AB  - We use post-war quarterly data for Belgium, Canada, Denmark, France, Germany, Greece, Ireland, Japan, the Netherlands, the United Kingdom and the United States to examine the Fisherian link between inflation and short-term nominal interest rates. In doing so, we apply the King and Watson (1997) methodology, paying particular attention to the integration and cointegration properties of the variables, since meaningful Fisher effect tests critically depend on such properties. We conclude that the data are generally rejecting the Fisher effect.
